{"build_type":"library","description":"Self-description hook baked into the front of every tool entry by the build. If argv index 1 equals the shell internal describe sentinel vehir-describe-contract-request, print the compile-time embedded contract text and return 1 (the injected prologue then returns so the tool does not run normal work); otherwise return 0 and the tool proceeds. GUARD: if argv is null, a raw kernel-entry invocation that passes a non-argv pointer, return 0 immediately so the entry runs its body without the prologue dereferencing a non-argv argument; this lets the loader invoke kernel entries. Reuses compare-paired-strings-octet-through-octet, decode-entire-source-building-document, write-result-object-toward-standard-output.","module_name":"generate-contract-textual-representation-answering-request","package_name":"generate-contract-textual-representation-answering-request","function_definitions":{"emit_contract_text_if_describe_requested":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"argv","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"text","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__cs_zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__cs_one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__cs_sixteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"allocate-character-buffer-inside-memory-arena","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"__cs_sixteen"}],"result_assignment_variable":"__cs_buf","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"__t0","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":